  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-07-25",
    "date": "2020-11-09T14:27:47Z",
    "text": "Protecting Access to Spinal Surgeries Act\n\nThis bill extends an exception to the application of site-neutral payment rates under the Medicare inpatient prospective payment system.\n\nCurrently, certain long-term care hospitals that primarily treat spinal cord injuries are excluded from such payment rates through FY2019 if they meet certain other criteria (e.g., a significant number of discharges of out-of-state patients in FY2014). The bill extends this exception through FY2024."
